- "Total budget" refers to the amount of money allocated to each category in the current budget;
- "Average rainfall from past seasons" is a metaphor for the average amount allocated to each category in historical budget data.

sql:
SELECT category_id, SUM(amount) as total_allocation
FROM budget_allocations
GROUP BY category_id;

SELECT category_name, subcategory 
FROM financial_categories 
WHERE parent_category_id IS NOT NULL;

SELECT category_name, subcategory, description
FROM financial_categories
WHERE category_id > 0;

